{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":468,"text":"How many of you have seen\nthe Alfred Hitchcock film \"The Birds\"?"},{"time":3841,"text":"Any of you get really freaked out by that?"},{"time":6538,"text":"You might want to leave now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7945,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":9000,"text":"So this is a vending machine for crows."},{"time":11027,"text":"Over the past few days,\nmany of you have been asking,"},{"time":13544,"text":"\"How did you come to this?\nHow did you get started doing this?\""},{"time":16558,"text":"It started, as with many great ideas,"},{"time":18351,"text":"or many ideas you can't\nget rid of, anyway,"},{"time":20411,"text":"at a cocktail party."},{"time":21590,"text":"About 10 years ago, I was at a cocktail\nparty with a friend of mine."},{"time":24824,"text":"We were sitting there,\nand he was complaining about the crows"},{"time":27737,"text":"that were all over his yard\nand making a big mess."},{"time":30132,"text":"And he was telling me\nwe ought to eradicate these things,"},{"time":32858,"text":"kill them, because they're making a mess."},{"time":34854,"text":"I said that was stupid,"},{"time":36029,"text":"maybe we should just train them\nto do something useful."},{"time":38626,"text":"And he said that was impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40181,"text":"And I'm sure I'm in good company\nin finding that tremendously annoying,"},{"time":43577,"text":"when someone tells you it's impossible."},{"time":45481,"text":"So I spent the next 10 years reading\nabout crows in my spare time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48635,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51435,"text":"And after 10 years of this, my wife said,"},{"time":53656,"text":"\"You've got to do this thing\nyou've been talking about,"},{"time":56300,"text":"and build the vending machine.\""},{"time":57819,"text":"So I did."},{"time":58994,"text":"But part of the reason\nI found this interesting is,"},{"time":61463,"text":"I started noticing that we're very\naware of all the species"},{"time":64319,"text":"that are going extinct on the planet"},{"time":66138,"text":"as a result of human habitation expansion,"},{"time":68231,"text":"and no one seems to be paying\nattention to all the species"},{"time":71200,"text":"that are actually living;\nthey're surviving."},{"time":73292,"text":"And I'm talking specifically\nabout synanthropic species,"},{"time":76041,"text":"which have adapted\nspecifically for human ecologies,"},{"time":78743,"text":"species like rats\nand cockroaches and crows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82130,"text":"And as I started looking at them,\nI was finding that they had hyper-adapted."},{"time":85768,"text":"They'd become extremely\nadept at living with us."},{"time":88184,"text":"And in return, we just tried\nto kill them all the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90881,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"And in doing so, we were\nbreeding them for parasitism."},{"time":94597,"text":"We were giving them all sorts\nof reasons to adapt new ways."},{"time":98582,"text":"So, for example, rats\nare incredibly responsive breeders."},{"time":101364,"text":"And cockroaches, as anyone who's tried\nto get rid of them knows,"},{"time":104407,"text":"have become really immune\nto the poisons that we're using."},{"time":107433,"text":"So I thought, let's build something\nthat's mutually beneficial;"},{"time":111091,"text":"something that we can both benefit from,"},{"time":113095,"text":"and find some way to make\na new relationship with these species."},{"time":116138,"text":"So I built the vending machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":117804,"text":"But the story of the vending machine\nis a little more interesting"},{"time":120898,"text":"if you know more about crows."},{"time":122309,"text":"It turns out, crows aren't just\nsurviving with human beings;"},{"time":125175,"text":"they're actually thriving."},{"time":126440,"text":"They're found everywhere\non the planet except for the Arctic"},{"time":129301,"text":"and the southern tip of South America."},{"time":131137,"text":"And in all that area,\nthey're only rarely found breeding"},{"time":133852,"text":"more than five kilometers\naway from human beings."},{"time":136195,"text":"So we may not think about them,\nbut they're always around."},{"time":138969,"text":"And not surprisingly,\ngiven the human population growth,"},{"time":141637,"text":"more than half of the human population\nis living in cities now."},{"time":144637,"text":"And out of those, nine-tenths\nof the human growth population"},{"time":147476,"text":"is occurring in cities."},{"time":148658,"text":"We're seeing a population boom with crows."},{"time":150855,"text":"So bird counts are indicating"},{"time":152924,"text":"that we might be seeing up to exponential\ngrowth in their numbers."},{"time":156096,"text":"So that's no great surprise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157767,"text":"But what was really interesting\nto me was to find out"},{"time":160284,"text":"that the birds were adapting\nin a pretty unusual way."},{"time":164281,"text":"And I'll give you an example of that."},{"time":166840,"text":"This is Betty.\nShe's a New Caledonian crow."},{"time":169134,"text":"And these crows use sticks in the wild"},{"time":171564,"text":"to get insects and whatnot\nout of pieces of wood."},{"time":174222,"text":"Here, she's trying to get\na piece of meat out of a tube."},{"time":176912,"text":"But the researchers had a problem."},{"time":178579,"text":"They messed up and left\njust a stick of wire in there."},{"time":181151,"text":"And she hadn't had the opportunity\nto do this before."},{"time":183698,"text":"You see, it wasn't working very well."},{"time":186190,"text":"So she adapted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188787,"text":"Now, this is completely unprompted;\nshe had never seen this done before."},{"time":192214,"text":"No one taught her to bend this into a hook"},{"time":194250,"text":"or had shown her how it could happen."},{"time":196055,"text":"But she did it all on her own."},{"time":197532,"text":"So keep in mind --\nshe's never seen this done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200017,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201632,"text":"Right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202839,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209498,"text":"Yeah. All right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210946,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215615,"text":"So that's the part where\nthe researchers freak out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":219913,"text":"It turns out,"},{"time":221104,"text":"we've been finding more and more\nthat crows are really intelligent."},{"time":224368,"text":"Their brains are in the same proportion\nas chimpanzee brains are."},{"time":228624,"text":"There's all kinds of anecdotes"},{"time":230090,"text":"for the different kinds\nof intelligence they have."},{"time":232476,"text":"For example, in Sweden,\ncrows will wait for fishermen"},{"time":235000,"text":"to drop lines through holes in the ice."},{"time":236917,"text":"And when the fishermen move off,"},{"time":238481,"text":"the crows fly down, reel up the lines,\nand eat the fish or the bait."},{"time":241746,"text":"It's pretty annoying for the fishermen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243708,"text":"On an entirely different tack,"},{"time":245171,"text":"at University of Washington\na few years ago,"},{"time":247785,"text":"they were doing an experiment where\nthey captured some crows on campus."},{"time":251169,"text":"Some students went out,\nnetted some crows, brought them in,"},{"time":254011,"text":"weighed and measured them,\nand let them back out again."},{"time":256619,"text":"And they were entertained to discover\nthat for the rest of the week,"},{"time":259855,"text":"whenever these particular students\nwalked around campus,"},{"time":262511,"text":"these crows would caw at them\nand run around,"},{"time":264646,"text":"and make their life kind of miserable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266482,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267508,"text":"They were significantly less entertained"},{"time":269477,"text":"when this went on for the next week."},{"time":271230,"text":"And the next month."},{"time":272527,"text":"And after summer break."},{"time":274279,"text":"Until they finally graduated\nand left campus,"},{"time":276602,"text":"and -- glad to get away, I'm sure --"},{"time":278366,"text":"came back sometime later, and found\nthe crows still remembered them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281629,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282659,"text":"So, the moral being: don't piss off crows."},{"time":284758,"text":"So now, students\nat the University of Washington"},{"time":288001,"text":"that are studying these crows,\ndo so with a giant wig and a big mask."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291397,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293636,"text":"It's fairly interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294970,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296565,"text":"So we know these crows are really smart,"},{"time":298513,"text":"but the more I dug into this,\nthe more I found"},{"time":300717,"text":"that they actually have\nan even more significant adaptation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304946,"text":"Video: Crows have become\nhighly skilled at making a living"},{"time":308384,"text":"in these new urban environments."},{"time":310755,"text":"In this Japanese city, they have devised\na way of eating a food"},{"time":314690,"text":"that normally they can't manage:"},{"time":319293,"text":"drop it among the traffic."},{"time":325303,"text":"The problem now is collecting the bits,\nwithout getting run over."},{"time":330468,"text":"Wait for the light to stop the traffic."},{"time":344609,"text":"Then, collect your cracked nut in safety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351702,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":354103,"text":"Joshua Klein: Yeah, pretty interesting."},{"time":356120,"text":"What's significant about this\nisn't that crows are using cars"},{"time":359081,"text":"to crack nuts."},{"time":360256,"text":"In fact, that's old hat for crows."},{"time":361921,"text":"This happened about 10 years ago"},{"time":363480,"text":"in a place called Sendai City,\nat a driving school"},{"time":366031,"text":"in the suburbs of Tokyo."},{"time":367737,"text":"And since that time,"},{"time":368916,"text":"all the crows in the neighborhood\nare picking up this behavior."},{"time":372002,"text":"Now every crow within five kilometers\nis standing by a sidewalk,"},{"time":375053,"text":"waiting to collect its lunch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376991,"text":"So they're learning from each other.\nAnd research bears this out."},{"time":380085,"text":"Parents seem to be teaching their young."},{"time":382623,"text":"They learn from their peers,\nthey learn from their enemies."},{"time":385497,"text":"If I have a little extra time,"},{"time":386976,"text":"I'll tell you about a case\nof crow infidelity"},{"time":389147,"text":"that illustrates that nicely."},{"time":391012,"text":"The point being, they've developed\ncultural adaptation."},{"time":393704,"text":"And as we heard yesterday,"},{"time":394973,"text":"that's the Pandora's box\nthat's getting human beings in trouble,"},{"time":398039,"text":"and we're starting to see it with them."},{"time":399936,"text":"They're able to very quickly\nand very flexibly adapt"},{"time":402496,"text":"to new challenges and new resources\nin their environment,"},{"time":405248,"text":"which is really useful\nif you live in a city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408681,"text":"So we know that there's lots of crows."},{"time":410787,"text":"We found out they're really smart\nand they can teach each other."},{"time":413872,"text":"When all this became clear,"},{"time":415197,"text":"I realized the only obvious thing to do\nis build a vending machine."},{"time":418384,"text":"So that's what we did."},{"time":419561,"text":"This is a vending machine for crows."},{"time":421322,"text":"And it uses Skinnerian training\nto shape their behavior over four stages."},{"time":425013,"text":"It's pretty simple."},{"time":426394,"text":"Basically, what happens\nis that we put this out in a field"},{"time":429422,"text":"or someplace where there's lots of crows."},{"time":431416,"text":"We put coins and peanuts\nall around the base of the machine."},{"time":434277,"text":"Crows eventually come by, eat the peanuts,"},{"time":436342,"text":"and get used to the machine being there."},{"time":438300,"text":"Eventually, they eat all the peanuts."},{"time":440105,"text":"Then they see peanuts\nhere on the feeder tray,"},{"time":442448,"text":"and hop up and help themselves."},{"time":444194,"text":"Then they leave, the machine\nspits up more coins and peanuts,"},{"time":447091,"text":"and life is dandy if you're a crow --"},{"time":448885,"text":"you can come back anytime\nand get yourself a peanut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451355,"text":"So when they get really used to that,\nwe move on to the crows coming back."},{"time":454864,"text":"Now they're used to the sound\nof the machine;"},{"time":456991,"text":"they keep coming back\nand digging out peanuts"},{"time":459127,"text":"from the pile of coins that's there."},{"time":460874,"text":"When they get really happy\nabout this, we stymie them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":463434,"text":"We move to the third stage,\nwhere we only give them a coin."},{"time":466252,"text":"Now, like most of us who have gotten\nused to a good thing,"},{"time":469014,"text":"this really pisses them off."},{"time":470377,"text":"So they do what they do in nature\nwhen they're looking for something:"},{"time":473681,"text":"sweep things out of the way\nwith their beak."},{"time":475778,"text":"They do that here, and that knocks\nthe coins down the slot."},{"time":478644,"text":"When that happens, they get a peanut."},{"time":480454,"text":"This goes on for some time."},{"time":481773,"text":"The crows learn that\nall they have to do is show up,"},{"time":484233,"text":"wait for the coin to come out,\nput it in the slot,"},{"time":486607,"text":"then get their peanut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487782,"text":"When they're good\nand comfortable with that,"},{"time":489885,"text":"we move to the final stage,\nwhere they show up and nothing happens."},{"time":493080,"text":"This is where we see the difference\nbetween crows and other animals."},{"time":496311,"text":"Squirrels, for example, would show up,\nlook for the peanut, go away."},{"time":500047,"text":"Come back, look for the peanut, go away."},{"time":502625,"text":"They do this maybe half a dozen times\nbefore they get bored,"},{"time":505487,"text":"and then they go off and play in traffic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507488,"text":"Crows, on the other hand,\nshow up and they try and figure it out."},{"time":511160,"text":"They know this machine\nhas been messing with them"},{"time":513489,"text":"through three different\nstages of behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515535,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":516561,"text":"They figure there must be more to it."},{"time":518364,"text":"So they poke at it and peck at it."},{"time":520197,"text":"And eventually some crow\ngets a bright idea:"},{"time":522375,"text":"\"Hey, there's lots of coins\nlying around from the first stage,"},{"time":526320,"text":"hops down, picks it up, drops it\nin the slot, and we're off to the races."},{"time":530509,"text":"That crow enjoys a temporary\nmonopoly on peanuts,"},{"time":532953,"text":"until his friends figure out\nhow to do it, and then there we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536620,"text":"So, what's significant about this to me"},{"time":539000,"text":"isn't that we can train crows\nto pick up peanuts."},{"time":541358,"text":"Mind you, there's 216 million\ndollars' worth of change lost every year,"},{"time":545212,"text":"but I'm not sure I can depend\non that ROI from crows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547891,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":548962,"text":"Instead, I think we should look\na little bit larger."},{"time":552170,"text":"I think crows can be trained\nto do other things."},{"time":554460,"text":"For example, why not train them\nto pick up garbage after stadium events?"},{"time":557960,"text":"Or find expensive components\nfrom discarded electronics?"},{"time":560888,"text":"Or maybe do search and rescue?"},{"time":563349,"text":"The main point of all this for me is,"},{"time":566000,"text":"we can find mutually beneficial\nsystems for these species."},{"time":568753,"text":"We can find ways to interact\nwith these other species"},{"time":571281,"text":"that doesn't involve exterminating them,"},{"time":573239,"text":"but involves finding an equilibrium\nwith them that's a useful balance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576565,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577844,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}